{{#demo-css}}
<h3>Component::<code>ui-nav-list</code></h3>

<h4>Overview</h4>
<div class="row">
    <desc>
        A <prop>nav list</prop> is a <prop>ui-selectable-list</prop> with cardinality defaulted to "1:1" and the skin set to "nav".
    </desc>
</div>
{{! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- }}

<h4>Interactive Demo</h4>
<row>
  <widget class="{{widgetWidth}}">
      {{ui-nav-list
        items=items
        position=position
        map=map
        size=size
        mood=mood
        onSelect='onSelect'
        onError='onError'
      }}
  </widget>
  <code>
  &nbsp;<br/>
    {{display-component componentName='ui-nav-list'
      items=':items'
      position=position
      map=':map'
      size=size
      mood=mood
      onSelect='onSelect'
      onError='onError'
    }}
  </code>
  <description>
    As stated in the overview, this component's behaviours are <i>largely</i> taken from the "selectable" list but with a navigation mention the cardinatlity, the min/max settings are preset as they typically would not need to be changed (you can override if you need to). Instead the main variables are:
    <h4>Positioning</h4>
    <controls>
      <control>
        <span class='title'>position</span>
        <span>{{radio-buttons buttons='left,right,top,bottom' defaultValue=0 value=position}}</span>
      </control>
    </controls>
    <p>
      If you have an item selected you'll see that all it's really doing is setting a <b>css</b> property which in turn puts the border highlighting to the appropriate side of the item.
    </p>
  </description>
</row>
<row>
  <description>
    <p>
      In the cases of switching to <i>top</i> or <i>bottom</i> you also get the flexbox switching direction and making the navigation horizontal.
    </p>
    <note>
      <b>Note:</b> contextually the <prop>position</prop> property is meant to signify where on the containers page this menu would be located <i>not</i> the location of the selected border.
    </note>

    <h4>Actions Up</h4>
    <p>
      Refer to the documentation for <a {{link-to 'demo-selectable-list'}}><prop>ui-selectable-list</prop></a>.
    </p>

  </description>
</row>

{{! ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- }}
<p class="downer">&nbsp;</p>

<configuration class="downer">
    <icon>{{icon-cog size="2x"}}</icon>
    <config>
        <columns>
            <column>
                List Size: <br/>
                {{ui-buttons cardinality='1:1' buttons='tiny,small,default,large,huge' value=size size='small' defaultValue='default'}}<br/>
            </column>
            <column>
                Mood:<br/>
                  {{ui-buttons cardinality='1:1' buttons='default,success,info,warning,error' value=mood disable=disableStaticChooser size='small' defaultValue='default'}}
             </column>
        </columns>
    </config>
</configuration>
{{/demo-css}}